Standard and Poor's Corp said itaffirmed the ratings on seven billion dlrs of debt andpreferred stock of American Telephone and Telegraph Co.    It said that despite flat revenues, ATT's interexchangebusiness and strong cash flow should sustain the current levelof debtholder protection for the next several years.    But ATT's overall competitive risk continues to grow as itextends beyond its traditional business area, S and P noted.Affirmed were ATT's AA debentures and preferred stock andA-1-plus commercial paper, and Pacific Telephone and TelegraphCo's AA debt which ATT assumed at divestiture. Reuter&#3;